TY  - JOUR
T1  - Strategic Human Resource Practices, Top Management Team Social Networks, and Firm Performance: The Role of Human Resource Practices in Creating Organizational Competitive Advantage
AU  - Collins, Christopher J.
AU  - Clark, Kevin D.
Y1  - 2003/12/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/30040665
DO  - 10.5465/30040665
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 740
EP  - 751
VL  - 46
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this article, we begin to explore the black box between human resources (HR) practices and firm performance. Specifically, we examine the relationships between a set of network-building HR practices, aspects of the external and internal social networks of top management teams, and firm performance. Results from a field study with 73 high-technology firms showed that the relationships between the HR practices and firm performance (sales growth and stock growth) were mediated through their top managers' social networks.
AB  - In this article, we begin to explore the black box between human resources (HR) practices and firm performance. Specifically, we examine the relationships between a set of network-building HR practices, aspects of the external and internal social networks of top management teams, and firm performance. Results from a field study with 73 high-technology firms showed that the relationships between the HR practices and firm performance (sales growth and stock growth) were mediated through their top managers' social networks.
