TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Customer Interaction Approach to Strategy and Production Complexity Alignment in Service Firms
AU  - Skaggs, Bruce C.
AU  - Huffman, Tammy Ross
Y1  - 2003/12/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/30040668
DO  - 10.5465/30040668
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 775
EP  - 786
VL  - 46
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study shows that the strategies of service firms affect the uncertainty they encounter in their dealings with customers. This strategically induced uncertainty then becomes the mechanism by which service firms organize their production processes. In a study of 234 service firms representing 96 different industries, we found strong support for relationships between these organizations' strategies and the level of complexity in their production processes. In addition, service firms that possessed the hypothesized fit between strategy and service production complexity tended to experience higher performance.
AB  - This study shows that the strategies of service firms affect the uncertainty they encounter in their dealings with customers. This strategically induced uncertainty then becomes the mechanism by which service firms organize their production processes. In a study of 234 service firms representing 96 different industries, we found strong support for relationships between these organizations' strategies and the level of complexity in their production processes. In addition, service firms that possessed the hypothesized fit between strategy and service production complexity tended to experience higher performance.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/30040668
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/30040668
Y2  - 2026/04/24
